# Arabidopsis thaliana Spaceflight Transcriptomic Analysis (OSD-678 / GLDS-612)

## Overview

This repository contains pathway-focused transcriptomic analyses of *Arabidopsis thaliana* grown aboard the International Space Station (ISS) and corresponding ground controls.

The study investigates how spaceflight conditions influence:

- Cryptochrome signaling
- Circadian clock regulation
- Reactive oxygen species (ROS) signaling
- Gibberellin metabolism and signaling
- Photosynthesis
- Photorespiration

The broader objective is to understand how spaceflight alters interconnected biological networks and to compare these responses with Near Null Magnetic Field (NMF) datasets.

